## render* and *output function pairs
To display content from the server.R file -> ui.R
must use a pair of render* and *Ouput functions

renderplot and plotoutput
- Base R plots and ggplot2 charts are rendered with the same functions
- @server.R file -> renderPlot
- @ui.R  -> plotOutput
- Modify size of output chart in plotOutput

rendertext and textoutput
- Display small text in only one style -> renderText,textOutput
- @server.R -> renderText
- @ui.R -> textOutput
- Complexs cases? renderUI/uiOutput

All htmlwidgets featured on |HTMLwidgets.org| can easily be displayed in shinyapps

Updating UI elements server-side required for many data-driven apps.
Why?
- Populate pull-down menus with specific values from dataset
- Interdependent controls, e.g.: filtering by continent
- Buiild reusable UI elements with Shiny modules
